        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 10:22PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1021 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northwest of Dodson, or 7 miles southeast of Wellington, moving
northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wellington and Dodson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
